FBIS4-8759 "dreeu074_i_94032" FBIS-EEU-94-074 Daily Report 17 Apr 1994 BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA Events in Gorazde -- 17 April Events in Gorazde -- 17 April Karadzic Comments on Agreement LD1704170194 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in Serbo-Croatian 1648 GMT 17 Apr 94 LD1704170194 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service Serbo-Croatian BFN [Text] Sarajevo, 17 Apr (TANJUG) -- Srpska republic president Radovan Karadzic said in Pale this evening that an agreement has been reached on an immediate cease-fire, "certain separation of the forces," and a maximum of restraint from military operations in the Gorazde area. After his talks with Yasushi Akashi, the UN secretary general's special envoy, Karadzic said that if the cease-fire is observed, it could be said that "we are coming closer to peace in Gorazde."
